3e\u0441\u043e\u0431\u0438\u0435 |trans-title=The holidays Culture of Health: Tutorial |location=[[Cheboksary]] |publisher=To Health via Culture |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/v7.html |isbn=978-5-88167-042-9 |language=Russian |accessdate=8 February 2019 |authormask=\u2014 with |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/761oUhngM |archivedate=8 February 2019}}\n{{Collapse bottom}}\n\n==Trivia==\n*According to a study conducted in 2015, Skumin was included in \"Russia team on medicine\". This list includes fifty-three famous Russian medical scientists from the [[Russia|Russian Federation]], the [[Soviet Union]], and the [[Russian Empire]] who were born in 1757\u20141950. Physicians of all specialities listed here. Among them [[Vladimir Bekhterev]], [[Vladimir Demikhov]], [[Sergei Korsakoff]], [[Ivan Pavlov]], [[Nikolay Pirogov]], [[Ivan Sechenov]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://medportal.ru/mednovosti/news/2015/04/21/466sbornaya/ |title=\u0421\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0435 |trans-title=Russia team on medicine |publisher=Medportal.ru |date=21 April 2015 |accessdate=16 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://farm.tatarstan.ru/rus/index.htm/news/420424.htm |title=\u0421\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0435 |trans-title=Russia team on medicine |publisher=Farm.tatarstan.ru |date=21 April 2015 |accessdate=16 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n*In the online poll \"The Name of Russia\", completed in 2017, Skumin by a wide margin is on first position in the section \"The Glory of Russia\". Also in the top 10 leaders in \"The Glory of Russia\" are [[Fyodor Dostoyevsky]], [[Alexander Pushkin]], [[Seraphim of Sarov]], [[Joseph Stalin]] (Jughashvili). At the same time Skumin is on fifteenth position in the section \"The Shame of Russia\". [[Mikhail Gorbachev]] and [[Boris Berezovsky (businessman)|Boris Berezovsky]] are in fourteenth and sixteenth positions in this list, and on the top of the rating \"The Shame of Russia\" are [[Alexander Lukashenko]] and [[Vladimir Putin]].<ref>{{cite book |author=Mari\u00eblle Wijermars |title=Memory Politics in Contemporary Russia: Television, Cinema and the State |isbn=9781138543195 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=Y7JjDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT153&lpg=PT153&dq=skumin+victor#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=27 September 2018 |date=2018-07-11}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=20em|\n* [[Agni Yoga]]\n* [[Open heart surgery#Risks|Open heart surgery]]\n* [[Penza Oblast#Notable people|Penza Oblast]]\n* [[Roerichism]]\n* [[Russian Cosmism]]\n* [[Skumin]]\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Victor Skumin}}\n\n* [https://hollis.harvard.edu/primo-explore/search?query=creator,exact,Skumin,%20V%20A,AND&tab=everything&search_scope=everything&sortby=rank&vid=HVD2&lang=en_US&mode=advanced&offset=0 Harvard Library: Skumin V A]\n* [http://kult-zdor.ru/?page_id=5 World Organisation of Culture of Health]\n* [https://biblmdkz.ru/index.html The Library of Culture of Health: Victor Skumin]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Skumin, Victor}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century philosophers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century philosophers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Russian writers]]\n[[Category:Cosmism]]\n[[Category:Cosmists]]\n[[Category:Holism]]\n[[Category:Kharkiv National Medical University people]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New Age writers]]\n[[Category:People from Penza Oblast]]\n[[Category:Psychiatry academics]]\n[[Category:Roerichism]]\n[[Category:Russian philosophers]]\n[[Category:Russian culture]]\n[[Category:Russian philosophy]]\n[[Category:Russian psychiatrists]]\n[[Category:Russian transhumanists]]\n[[Category:Russians in Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Soviet psychiatrists]]\n[[Category:Soviet scientists]]\n[[Category:Spiritual evolution]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name = Victor Skumin<br>\u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0421\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0438\u043d\n| image = \u0421\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0456\u043d \u0412\u0456\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0456\u0439\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 01.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Victor Skumin, 2016\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1948|08|30}}\n| birth_place = [[Pensa Oblast#Notable people|Pensa Oblast]], [[RSFSR]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| residence   = [[Soviet Union]], [[Russian Federation]] \n| nationality  = [[Soviet people|Soviet]], [[Russian people|Russian]]\n| fields       = [[Psychiatry]], [[psychotherapy]], [[psychology]], [[philosophy]] \n| workplaces   = [[Kiev]] Institute of Cardiovascular Surgery ([[:ru:\u041d\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0442 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0435\u0447\u043d\u043e-\u0441\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0439 \u0445\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0438\u0438 \u0438\u043c. \u041d. \u041c. \u0410\u043c\u043e\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u0410\u041c\u041d \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043d\u044b|ru]]), [[Kharkiv Medical Academy of Post-graduate Education]], [[Kharkiv State Academy of Culture]], [[Rerikhism#The World Organisation of Culture of Health (WOCH)|The World Organisation of Culture of Health]] ([[Moscow]])\n| alma_mater    = [[Kharkiv National Medical University]]\n| known_for     = [[:fr:Syndrome de Skumin|Skumin syndrome]]\n| website = {{URL|https://biblmdkz.ru/skumin.html}}\n}}\n\n'''Victor Andreevich Skumin''' ({{lang-rus|\u0412\u0438\u0301\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0301\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0421\u043a\u0443\u0301\u043c\u0438\u043d|p=\u02c8v\u02b2ikt\u0259r \u0250n\u02c8dr\u02b2ej\u026av\u02b2\u026at\u0255 \u02c8skum\u02b2\u026an}}, born 30 August 1948) is a [[Russian scientists#Physicians and psychologists|Russian and Soviet scientist]], [[psychiatrist]], [[philosopher]] and [[writer]].\n\nAfter graduating from the [[Kharkiv National Medical University]] in 1973, in 1976, he became a psychotherapist in [[Kiev Institute of Cardiovascular Surgery]]. In 1978, he described a new [[disease]], the [[Skumin syndrome]]. He introduced a method of [[psychotherapy]] and [[Self-help|self-improvement]] based on [[optimism|optimistic]] [[autosuggestion]] for psychological rehabilitation of [[Cardiac surgery|cardiosurgical]] [[patient]]s (1979).\n\nFrom 1980 to 1990, he was professor of psychotherapy at the [[Kharkiv Medical Academy of Post-graduate Education]]. The main result of his scientific activity was the discovery of the \"syndrome of the neurotic phantom of somatic disease\" and a \"concept of the mental constituent of a chronic somatic disease\".\n\nFrom 1990 to 1994, Skumin held positions as Professor by the Chair of [[Psychology]] and [[Pedagogy]], and Professor by the Chair of [[Physical Education]] and Health life at the [[Kharkiv State Academy of Culture]]. In 1994, he was elected to the post of the President-founder of the [[World Organisation of Culture of Health]] ([[Moscow]]). In 1995, Skumin became the first [[editor-in-chief]] of the journal ''[[To Health via Culture]]''. He is known for inventing a popular [[Terminology|term]]  \"Culture of Health\" (1968).\n\nBesides [[psychiatry]] and psychology, Skumin writes on [[Self care|healthy lifestyle]], [[Yoga in Russia|yoga]], and [[philosophy]]. He co-authored series of illustrated books and articles on [[Agni Yoga]], [[Roerichism]], [[Russian cosmism]], [[Transhumanism]], and [[New Age]]. He wrote books of fiction and lyrics for several songs.\n\n==Early life and education==\n{{multiple image\n| align = left\n| image1 =\n| width1 = 150 \n| alt1 = \n| caption1 = \n| image2 =\n| width2 = 195 \n| alt2 = \n| caption2 = \n| footer = Victor Skumin (center) as a [[Vladimir Lenin All-Union Pioneer Organization|young pioneer]] at [[Petrozavodsk]]\n}}\n\n\nVictor Skumin<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pronouncekiwi.com/Victor%20Skumin |title=How To Pronounce Victor Skumin |publisher=pronouncekiwi |accessdate=4 September 2019}}</ref> was born on 30 August 1948 in [[Penza Oblast#Notable people|Penza Oblast]], [[RSFSR]], where his father \u2013 Andrew [[Skumin]] ({{lang-rus|\u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0301\u0439 \u0421\u043a\u0443\u0301\u043c\u0438\u043d|p=\u0250n\u02c8dr\u02b2ej \u02c8skum\u02b2\u026an}}) \u2013 was an [[Officer (armed forces)|officer]] of [[Ministry of State Security (Soviet Union)|MGB of the USSR]].<ref name=\"Professor Victor A. Skumin\">{{cite web |url=http://kult-zdor.ru/?page_id=163 |title=Professor Victor A. Skumin |publisher=Kult-zdor.ru |accessdate=19 December 2017 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6voEAKNpB?url=http://kult-zdor.ru/?page_id=163 |archivedate=18 December 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Victor Skumin\">{{cite web |url=https://biblmdkz.ru/skumin.html |title=Victor Skumin |publisher=biblmdkz.ru |accessdate=4 September 2019 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/76agVQY4L |archivedate=3 March 2019 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref> After the birth of Victor, the family moved to the city of [[Kazan]], where his father was appointed to the post of Chairman of the [[Military Tribunal]] of the [[Internal Troops of Russia|Internal Troops]] of the [[Volga Military District]].<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.archive.gov.tatarstan.ru/magazine/go/anonymous/main/?path=mg:/numbers/2002_3_4/03/03_7/ |first=Alter |last=Litvin |title=\u042f\u043f\u043e\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0432\u043e\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u043f\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435: \u0441\u043f\u0435\u0446\u043b\u0430\u0433\u0435\u0440\u044c \u043d\u0430 \u041a\u0430\u043c\u0435 |trans-title=Japanese prisoners of war: special camp on the Kama river |journal=Gasyrlar Avazy=\u0116kho Vekov |year=2002 |volume=3/4 |oclc=33252147 |issn=2073-7483 |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wARmce07?url=http://www.archive.gov.tatarstan.ru/magazine/go/anonymous/main/?path=mg%3A%2Fnumbers%2F2002_3_4%2F03%2F03_7%2F |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref> \n\nThe family many times moved from one city to another, where Andrew Skumin was appointed to a new post. These cities, in particular, were [[Penza]], [[Chelyabinsk]], and [[Petrozavodsk]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://chgvs.chel.sudrf.ru/modules.php?name=info_court&id=14 |title=\u0421\u043e\u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0427\u0435\u043b\u044f\u0431\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0433\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0437\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0432\u043e\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430 (\u0432\u043e\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0440\u0438\u0431\u0443\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0430) |trans-title=The modern history of the Chelyabinsk garrison military court (military tribunal) |publisher=chgvs.chel.sudrf.ru |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6ezifI12O?url=http://chgvs.chel.sudrf.ru/modules.php?name=info_court&id=14 |archivedate=2 February 2016 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"Victor Skumin\"/> For this reason, he studied in various [[educational institutions]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://famous-birthdays.ru/data/30_avgusta/skumin_viktor_andreevich.html|title=\u0421\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0438\u043d \u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447|trans-title=Skumin Victor Andreevich|publisher=famous-birthdays.ru|accessdate=24 December 2017|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6vxEw5vwf?url=http://famous-birthdays.ru/data/30_avgusta/skumin_viktor_andreevich.html|archivedate=24 December 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nSkumin studied [[medicine]] at the [[Kharkiv National Medical University]]. The history of the higher medical school in [[Kharkiv]] is more than 200 years long and closely connected with the history of [[University of Kharkiv|Vasily Karazin Kharkiv National University]], because it sprang from its Medical Faculty. The University \u2013 one of the oldest University of the [[Russian Empire]] and the [[Soviet Union]] \u2013 was founded in 1804, a decree about its foundation was signed by the [[Emperor of Russia]] [[Alexander I of Russia|Alexander I]], and the first Statutes of the University were approved at that time. In the Kharkiv University were laid high scientific standards. Its history is connected with the names of the [[List of Nobel laureates|Nobel Laureates]] \u2013 [[Lev Landau#National Scientific Center Kharkov Institute of Physics and Technology, Kharkiv|Lev Landau]], [[Simon Kuznets#Biography|Simon Kuznets]], [[\u00c9lie Metchnikoff#Biography|\u00c9lie Metchnikoff]] \u2013 and other distinguished scientists.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.univer.kharkov.ua/en/general/our_university/history |title=Kharkov National University (Official Site) |publisher=Univer. Kharkov.en |accessdate=24 December 2017 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6vxFPdn1i?url=http://www.univer.kharkov.ua/en/general/our_university/history |archivedate=24 December 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://knmu.kharkov.ua/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=298&Itemid=10&lang=en |title=Kharkov National Medical University |publisher=Knmu.kharkov.ua |accessdate=24 December 2017 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6vxFieT7n?url=http://knmu.kharkov.ua/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=298&Itemid=10&lang=en |archivedate=24 December 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nSkumin graduated the Medical University in 1973 with diploma with honours.<ref name=\"Professor Victor A. Skumin\"/> In 1968, when he was still a [[Medical school#Medical students|medical student]], he proposed the [[Terminology|term]]  ''Culture of Health''  ({{lang-ru|\u041a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0301\u0440\u0430 \u0417\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0301\u0432\u044c\u044f}}),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://900igr.net/prezentatsii/fizkultura/Kultura-zdorovja/006-Vpervye-termin-kultura-zdorovja-obosnoval-i-vvel-v-upotreblenie-v.html |year=2009 |author=Kovaleva E. A. |title=\u041f\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0441\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442. \u041a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430 \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u044f \u0443\u0447\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0445\u0441\u044f \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0444\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0441\u0431\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0433\u0430\u044e\u0449\u0435\u0439 \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0434\u044b \u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044b. \u0421\u043b\u0430\u0439\u0434 6 |trans-title=Pedagogical Council. Slide 6 of the presentation \"culture of health\" to the lessons of physical education on the theme the \"Health\" |publisher=900igr.net |accessdate=24 December 2017 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6vxG80Rkg?url=http://900igr.net/prezentatsii/fizkultura/Kultura-zdorovja/006-Vpervye-termin-kultura-zdorovja-obosnoval-i-vvel-v-upotreblenie-v.html |archivedate=24 December 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Culture of health\">{{cite web |url=http://ru.science.wikia.com/wiki/%D0%9A%D1%83%D0%BB%D1%8C%D1%82%D1%83%D1%80%D0%B0_%D0%B7%D0%B4%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D1%8C%D1%8F |title=\u041a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430 \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u044f |trans-title=Culture of health |publisher=ru.science.wikia.com |accessdate=24 December 2017 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6vxGZi5AX?url=http://ru.science.wikia.com/wiki/%D0%9A%D1%83%D0%BB%D1%8C%D1%82%D1%83%D1%80%D0%B0_%D0%B7%D0%B4%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D1%8C%D1%8F |archivedate=24 December 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> which has become widespread.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.umsystem.edu/totalrewards/wellness/culture_of_health |title=Culture of Health |publisher=Unsystem.edu |accessdate=24 December 2017 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6vxH89CKi?url=https://www.umsystem.edu/totalrewards/wellness/culture_of_health |archivedate=24 December 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://intkonf.org/moyseyuk-vp-suchasni-pidhodi-do-vivchennya-fenomenu-kulturi-zdorovya/ |year=2012 |author=Mojse\u00fbk V. P. |title=\u0421\u043e\u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0445\u043e\u0434\u044b \u043a \u0438\u0437\u0443\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044e \u0444\u0435\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u043a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u044b \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u044f |trans-title=Modern approach to the study of the phenomenon of Culture of Health |publisher=intkonf.org |accessdate=24 December 2017 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6vxIrInZl?url=http://intkonf.org/moyseyuk-vp-suchasni-pidhodi-do-vivchennya-fenomenu-kulturi-zdorovya/ |archivedate=24 December 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The main task of a Culture of Health is to implement innovative health programs that support a holistic approach to physical, mental and spiritual well-being.<ref name=\"Professor Victor A. Skumin\"/>\n\nVictor Skumin is married. He has two sons \u2013 Andrew and Maxim, as well as granddaughter Alice Skumina and grandson Alexey Skumin.<ref name=\"Victor Skumin\"/>\n\n==Contribution to psychiatry and psychotherapy==\n=== Cardiac surgery ===\nHe researched from 1976 to 1980 psychological and psychiatric problems of [[Cardiac surgery#Risks|cardiac surgery]] under the mentorship of [[Nikolai Amosov#Biography|Nikolai Amosov]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ukraine-in.ua/en/science/velikie-ukainskie-mediki|title=Ukrainian doctors which changed the world|publisher=Ukraine-in.ua|accessdate=2 January 2018|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAMyYcTU?url=http://ukraine-in.ua/en/science/velikie-ukainskie-mediki|archivedate=2 January 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> who was the founder and first director of the [[:ru:\u041d\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0442\u0443\u0442 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0435\u0447\u043d\u043e-\u0441\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0439 \u0445\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0438\u0438 \u0438\u043c. \u041d. \u041c. \u0410\u043c\u043e\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u0410\u041c\u041d \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043d\u044b|Kiev Institute of Cardiovascular Surgery]]. This Institute was the first to conduct surgical treatment of heart diseases in the [[Ukrainian SSR]] (since 1955), the Institute began to conduct operations with [[extracorporeal]] circulation (1958), and [[mitral valve replacement]]s (1963). In 1961, Amosov was awarded [[Lenin Prize]] for the work of surgery.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://amosovinstitute.org.ua/?hist&en |title=History of the Institute |publisher=Amosovinstitute.org.ua |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6gqKB2VHQ?url=http://amosovinstitute.org.ua/?hist&en |archivedate=17 April 2016 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://24tv.ua/home/showSingleNews.do?amosov_pervim_provel_protezirovanie_klapana_na_serdtse&objectId=389630&lang=ru |title=\u0410\u043c\u043e\u0441\u043e\u0432 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u043c \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0451\u043b \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043a\u043b\u0430\u043f\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0430 |trans-title=Amosov was the first Soviet surgeon, who held heart valve replacement |location=Kiev |publisher=[[:uk:24 (\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b)|\u0422\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b \u00ab24\u00bb]]: Tell about Ukraine |date=7 December 2013 |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAOlKTJd?url=https://24tv.ua/ru/amosov_pervim_provel_protezirovanie_klapana_na_serdtse_n389630 |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nSince a valve replacement is a [[heart]] surgical procedure, it requires placing the patient on [[cardiopulmonary bypass]]. With a valve replacement surgery, there are some [[Mitral valve replacement#Risks|risks]]. Skumin researched a neuropsychological and psychopathologic changes following [[Open heart surgery#Risks|open heart surgery]], nonpsychotic mental disorders in [[patient]]s with [[valvular heart disease]] before and after surgery, associated with [[Artificial heart valve#Mechanical valves|mechanical artificial heart valve (MHV)]] implant.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Kondyukova N.V. |author2=Rutkovskaya N.V. |author3=Barbarash O.L. |url=https://cyberleninka.ru/article/n/kachestvo-zhizni-integralnyy-pokazatel-effektivnosti-lecheniya-vozmozhnosti-ego-ispolzovaniya-u-patsientov-s-porokami-klapanov-serdtsa |title=\u041a\u0430\u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0436\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0438 \u2013 \u0438\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c \u044d\u0444\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u043b\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f, \u0432\u043e\u0437\u043c\u043e\u0436\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0435\u0433\u043e \u0438\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0443 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u0441 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043a\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u043a\u043b\u0430\u043f\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0430 |trans-title=Quality of life as an integral indicator of successful treatment, opportunities of its use in patients with valvular heart disease |publisher=[[:ru:\u0421\u0438\u0431\u0438\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b|Siberian Medical Journal]] ([[Irkutsk]]) |year=2015 |number=6 |pages=38 |issn=1815-7572 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6g0TCsW4l?url=http://smj.ismu.baikal.ru/jour/article/download/942/949 |archivedate=14 March 2016 |accessdate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Graphic of the SynCardia temporary Total Artificial Heart beside a human heart.jpg |left |270px |thumb |<center>Total [[Artificial Heart]] beside a human heart</center>]]\n\nAn artificial heart valve is a device [[Implant (medicine)|implanted]] in the heart of a patient with valvular heart disease, [[congenital heart defect]], etc. When one or two of the four [[heart valve]]s malfunctions, the medical choice may be to replace the natural valve with an artificial valve. There are three major types of mechanical valves with many modifications on these designs. This requires [[Cardiac surgery|open heart surgery]]. The mechanical valves are made from metal and [[pyrolytic carbon]], and can last a lifetime. All MHV function in the human body creating a unique sound effects and vibration. Patients with mechanical valves must take blood-thinning medications to prevent [[thrombus|clot]]ting. The choice of which valve type to use depends upon the patient's age, medical condition, preferences with medication, and lifestyle.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sundt |first=Thoralf M. |title=Mitral Valve Repair |url=http://ctsurgerypatients.org/adult-heart-disease/mitral-valve-disease |publisher=The Society of Thoracic Surgeons |accessdate=2 January 2018 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6gqKq5Z3O?url=http://ctsurgerypatients.org/adult-heart-disease/mitral-valve-disease |archivedate=17 April 2016 |df=dmy-all |date=2015-08-14 }}</ref>\n[[:fr:Syndrome de Skumin|''Skumin syndrome'']] ({{lang-ru|\u0421\u0438\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0301\u043c \u0421\u043a\u0443\u0301\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430}}) was described by Skumin in 1978 as a ''cardioprosthetic psychopathological syndrome'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://info-farm.ru/alphabet_index/p/psikhiatriya.html |publisher=info-farm.ru |title=\u0418\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u044f \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u0438\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0438 |trans-title=History of psychiatry |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAWi5Y81?url=http://info-farm.ru/alphabet_index/p/psikhiatriya.html |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> associated with mechanical heart valve implant and manifested by [[Fear#Fear of the unknown|irrational fear]], [[anxiety]], [[Depression (mood)|depression]] and [[sleep disorder]].<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/articles/j18_3.html |year=2010 |last=Bobina |first=L. A. |title=\u0421\u0438\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u043c \u0421\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u043d\u043e\u0437\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430 |trans-title=The Skumin syndrome as a nosological form |journal=To Health Via Culture |volume=18 |pages=22\u201336 |issn=0204-3440 |oclc=70966742 |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAX2xo3L?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/articles/j18_3.html |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> This [[syndrome]] is often accompanied by [[asthenia]].<ref name=\"Bobina\">{{cite web |url=http://kult-zdor.ru/?page_id=906 |title=Skumin syndrome |publisher=Kult-zdor.ru |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAXVBxvG?url=http://kult-zdor.ru/?page_id=906 |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"Andrea Ruzza\">{{cite journal |first=Andrea |last=Ruzza |title=Nonpsychotic mental disorder after open heart surgery|journal=[[Asian Cardiovascular and Thoracic Annals]] |volume = 22|issue=3 |pages=374 |date=16 October 2013 |df=dmy-all |doi=10.1177/0218492313493427 |pmid=24585929 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |script-title=ru: Nepsikhoticheskie narusheniia psikhiki u bol'nykh s priobretennymi porokami serdtsa do i posle operatsii (obzor) |trans-title=Nonpsychotic mental disorders in patients with acquired heart defects before and after surgery (review) |year=1982 |journal=[[:ru:\u0416\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b \u043d\u0435\u0432\u0440\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0438 \u0438 \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u0438\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0438 \u0438\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0421. \u0421. \u041a\u043e\u0440\u0441\u0430\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430|Zhurnal nevropatologii i psikhiatrii imeni S.S. Korsakova]] |volume=82 |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/articles/nmd.html |oclc=112979417 |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAYHGzbC?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/articles/nmd.html |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> [[Alain Carpentier]] \u2013 a member of the [[French Academy of Sciences]] and the head the Department of Cardiovascular Surgery at the [[H\u00f4pital Europ\u00e9en Georges-Pompidou]] in Paris \u2013 believed in 2011 that Skumin syndrome develops in a quarter of the patients with an artificial heart valve.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://wikimonde.com/article/Syndrome_de_Skoumine |title=Syndrome de Skoumine |trans-title=Skumin syndrome |publisher=wikimonde.com |language=French |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAYawAue?url=https://wikimonde.com/article/Syndrome_de_Skoumine |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> It is possible that a similar problem arises in the conduct of operations to implement an [[artificial heart]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://progavrichenko.ru/reabilitaciya-invalidov/novosti-mediciny/iskusstvennye-serdca-pochemu-oni-tak-bystro-ostanavlivayutsya.html |title=\u0418\u0441\u043a\u0443\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0430. \u041f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u043e\u043d\u0438 \u0442\u0430\u043a \u0431\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0438\u0432\u0430\u044e\u0442\u0441\u044f? |trans-title=Artificial hearts. Why are they stops so quick? |publisher=progavrichenko.ru |date=7 March 2014 |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAZJm3F5?url=http://progavrichenko.ru/reabilitaciya-invalidov/novosti-mediciny/iskusstvennye-serdca-pochemu-oni-tak-bystro-ostanavlivayutsya.html |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://fsds.org.ua/?p=890 |title=\u0418\u0441\u043a\u0443\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0435 |trans-title=Artificial heart |publisher=fsds.org.ua |date=16 November 2010 |accessdate=2 January 2018 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6grS2Mz9j?url=http://fsds.org.ua/?p=890 |archivedate=18 April 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nThe Russia's international news agency ''[[RIA Novosti]]'', operating under the purview of the Russian [[Ministry of Communications and Mass Media (Russia)|Ministry of Communications and Mass Media]], wrote about this problem (2014),<ref>{{cite web |last=Petukhov |first=Sergei |script-title=ru: \u041f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0438\u0432\u0430\u044e\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0438\u0441\u043a\u0443\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0430 |trans-title=Why the artificial hearts to doing the stops |year=2014 |location=Moscow |publisher=[[RIA Novosti]]: Legal alert |url=http://ria.ru/analytics/20140304/998134091.html |language=Russian |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAa8k0Sf?url=https://ria.ru/analytics/20140304/998134091.html |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|Victor Skumin, our domestic scientist, described \"cardioprosthetic psychopathologic syndrome\", which entered the textbooks as \"Skumin syndrome\". The human mind is constantly fixed on the motor is running. For example, in contrast to prosthetic of teeth, arms or legs, it is not possible to divert attention  of human from the sounds of functioning implant in his body. Person is constantly waiting for a suddenly the motor will stop? In the human heart the pain gives signals. Here there is no pain and can not to be. In the future, probably, there will be heart prostheses, imitating his heartbeat. But they will not be hurt, and Skumin syndrome will continue to hang over the human psyche with a heart valve prosthesis.}}\n\nThe methods and the main principles of such [[therapy]] and [[neuropsychological rehabilitation]] are described and its efficacy was demonstrated.<ref>{{cite book |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |script-title=ru: \u041f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0438\u044f \u0438 \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0432 \u0441\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043c\u0435 \u0440\u0435\u0430\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0441 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0437\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u043a\u043b\u0430\u043f\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0430: \u041c\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 |trans-title=Psychotherapy and psychoprophylaxis in the rehabilitation of the patients with prosthetic heart valves: Methodical recommendations |year=1980 |location=[[Kiev]] |publisher=[[Ministry of Healthcare (Ukraine)|Ministry of Healthcare of Ukrainian SSR]] |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m12.html |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAo0FQtD?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m12.html |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last2=Skumin |first2=V. A. |last1=Filatov |first1=A. T. |year=1985 |script-title=ru: \u041f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0438 \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0438\u044f \u0432 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0438\u043e\u0445\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0438\u0438 |trans-title=Psychoprophylaxis and psychotherapy in cardiac surgery |location=[[Kiev]] |publisher=[[:uk:\u0417\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432'\u044f (\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0435 \u0432\u0438\u0434\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0442\u0432\u043e)|Zdorovja]]: Medical Practitioners Library |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m6.html |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAoMtS9I?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m6.html |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Skumin proposed [[mixture]] subsequently named after him. [[:tt:\u0421\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0438\u043d \u043c\u0438\u043a\u0441\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0441\u044b|Skumin\u2019s mixture]] ({{lang-ru|\u041c\u0438\u043a\u0441\u0442\u0443\u0301\u0440\u0430 \u0421\u043a\u0443\u0301\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430}}) is a medicine with a sedative effect, affecting the [[central nervous system]]. It is used to treat Skumin syndrome, light forms of heart failure, anxiety and sleep disorders, and asthenia.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/articles/j24_3.html |title=\u041c\u0438\u043a\u0441\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430 \u0421\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430 |trans-title=Skumin\u2019s mixture |author=Sergeeva NL |year=2015 |journal=To Health Via Culture |volume=24 |pages=14\u201338 |issn=0204-3440 |accessdate=2 January 2018}}</ref> The medicine is known to be well tolerated, with no contra-indications, except sensitivity. The formula contains [[Adonis vernalis]], [[Crataegus]], [[Valerian root]], [[Leonurus cardiaca]], [[Eucalyptus]],  [[Peppermint]], and [[Rose hip]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oriur.ru/kultura-zdorovie/mikstura-v-a-skumina.html |title=\u041c\u0438\u043a\u0441\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430 \u0421\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0430 |trans-title=Skumin\u2019s mixture |publisher=oriur.ru |accessdate=2 January 2018 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6gwNtwQhn?url=http://www.oriur.ru/kultura-zdorovie/mikstura-v-a-skumina.html |archivedate=21 April 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nFor psychological rehabilitation, Skumin improved psychological function by calming the nervous system, enhancing relaxation, increasing body awareness and decreasing general anxiety.<ref name=\"Andrea Ruzza\"/><ref>{{cite journal |last3=Skumin |first3=V. A. |last2=Morozov |first2=S. M. |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/articles/kardiologiia.html |last1=Bendet |first1=Ya. A. |title=Psychological aspects of the rehabilitation of patients after the surgical treatment of heart defects |year=1980 |script-title=ru: Psikhologicheskie aspekty reabilitatsii bol'nykh posle khirurgicheskogo lecheniia porokov serdtsa |trans-title=Psychological aspects of the rehabilitation of patients after the surgical treatment of heart defects |journal=Kardiologiia |volume=20 |issue=6 |pages=45\u201351 |oclc=114137678 |pmid=7392405 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAuZ2Ar5?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/articles/kardiologiia.html |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn 1979, Skumin created a special modification of mind control method for psychological rehabilitation of cardiosurgical patients.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ru.science.wikia.com/wiki/\u041f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433_\u043f\u043e_\u0421\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0443 |title=\u041f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433 \u043f\u043e \u0421\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0443 |trans-title=Skumin mind control method |publisher=ru.science.wikia.com |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wAxfYdsd?url=http://ru.science.wikia.com/wiki/%D0%9F%D1%81%D0%B8%D1%85%D0%BE%D1%82%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%B3_%D0%BF%D0%BE_%D0%A1%D0%BA%D1%83%D0%BC%D0%B8%D0%BD%D1%83 |archivedate=2 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |script-title=ru: \u0418\u0441\u043a\u0443\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433\u0430 \u0438 \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435 |trans-title=The art of mind control for healthy lifestyle |year=1993 |location=[[Kharkiv]] |publisher=To Health via Culture |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/is.html |language=Russian |isbn=978-5-86389-002-9 |accessdate=2 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6t5T4p9x0?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/is.html |archivedate=29 August 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> This method is based on [[autogenic training]]. Autogenic training is a [[relaxation technique]] developed by the psychiatrist [[Johannes Heinrich Schultz]]. He emphasized parallels to techniques in [[yoga]] and [[meditation]]. It is a method for influencing one's [[autonomic nervous system]]. The technique involves the daily practice of sessions that last around 15 minutes, usually in the morning, at lunch time, and in the evening. During each session, the practitioner will repeat a set of visualisations that induce a state of [[Relaxation (psychology)|relaxation]]. Each session can be practiced in a position chosen amongst a set of recommended postures.<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Stetter F, Kupper S |title=Autogenic training: a meta-analysis of clinicaloutcome studies |journal=Applied Psychophysiology and Biofeedback |volume=27 |issue=1 |pages=45\u201398 |date=March 2002 |pmid=12001885 |doi=10.1023/A:1014576505223}}</ref>\n\nThe technique of the [[:tt:\u0421\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0447\u0430 \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433|Skumin mind control method]] ({{lang-ru|\u041f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0301\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433 \u043f\u043e \u0421\u043a\u0443\u0301\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0443}}) involves the use of two standard postures: sitting meditation and lying down meditation. This method of psychotraining includes five psychological exercises: the first is \"the relaxation\", the second one is \"the warming\", the third one is \"the zero gravity\", the fourth one is \"the target [[autosuggestion]]\", and the fifth exercise is \"the psychological activation\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://psychology.wikia.com/wiki/Skumin_mind_control_method |title=Skumin mind control method |publisher=psychology.wikia.com |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDBhn4b8?url=http://psychology.wikia.com/wiki/Skumin_mind_control_method |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Each session contain explanation of the theory and practice of each new exercise as it is reached. The therapeutic effect is achieved by the neutralization of traumatic emotional experiences and the progressive reorganization of the psychic structures to include previously unacceptable mental contents, too.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://progavrichenko.ru/reabilitaciya-invalidov/psixotrening-po-skuminu.html |title=\u041f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433 \u043f\u043e \u0421\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0438\u043d\u0443 |trans-title=Skumin mind control method |publisher=progavrichenko.ru |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDC69hxz?url=http://progavrichenko.ru/reabilitaciya-invalidov/psixotrening-po-skuminu.html |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Rivera |first1=J. L. G. de |url=http://www.psicoter.es/_arts/pdf/01_A166_01.pdf |title=Autogenic An\u00e1lisis: The tool Freud was looking for |journal=International Journal of Psychotherapy |year=2001 |volume=6 |pages=67\u201376 |accessdate=4 January 2018 |doi=10.1080/13569080124247 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDEfjBEX?url=http://www.psicoter.es/_arts/pdf/01_A166_01.pdf |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref> This method of psychotherapy has found application in medical practice, in particular in the treatment of [[phobia]]s, [[headach]]es, etc.<ref>{{YouTube|Wl4Qm4bbs_k|Skumin's doctrine of the culture of health: Phobias. Part 1}} {{in lang|ru}} \n* {{YouTube|c1pZ3yYX8HU |\u2014 Part 2}} {{in lang|ru}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|b8n2AKeOaK0|Skumin's doctrine of the culture of health: Headache. Part 1.}} {{in lang|ru}} \n* {{YouTube|w1Ry-KlNxJk|\u2014 Part 2.}} {{in lang|ru}}</ref>\n\nSkumin's priority on the description of this syndrome and the establishment of effective methods of treatment and rehabilitation of cardiosurgical patients confirmed [[Nikolai Amosov]] and [[:ru:\u0411\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0435\u0442, \u042f\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u0410\u0431\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447|Yakov Bendet]],<ref>{{cite book |last2=Bendet |first2=Ya. A. |last1=Amosov |first1=N. M. |year=1983 |script-title=ru: \u0422\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0435\u0432\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0430\u0441\u043f\u0435\u043a\u0442\u044b \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0438\u043e\u0445\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0440\u0433\u0438\u0438 |trans-title=Therapeutic aspects of cardiac surgery |location=[[Kiev]] |publisher=[[:uk:\u0417\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432'\u044f (\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0435 \u0432\u0438\u0434\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0442\u0432\u043e)|Zdorovja]] |url=http://biblus.ru/Default.aspx?book=6m056m4a5 |language=Russian |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDFGTtgN?url=http://biblus.ru/Default.aspx?book=6m056m4a5 |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> [[Alain Carpentier]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://heartforyoursoul.com/ |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/68WpPuzqR?url=http://heartforyoursoul.com/ |archivedate=19 June 2012 |title=About artificial heart |publisher=Heart For Your Soul |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.medvestnik.by/ru/issues/a_10922.html |author=Bizunkov, A. |title=\u0417\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043c \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a\u0443 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0435 |trans-title=What for a man need a heart |publisher=Medvestnik.by |date=3 October 2014 |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDFgf8lm?url=http://www.medvestnik.by/ru/sovremennii_podxod/view/zachem-cheloveku-serdtse-12295-2014/ |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and many others.<ref name=\"Andrea Ruzza\"/><ref>{{cite book |last1=Bacherikov |first1=N. E. |script-title=ru: \u041a\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u0438\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0438\u044f |trans-title=Clinical Psychiatry |year=1989 |location=[[Kiev]] |url=http://www.psyoffice.ru/page,8,3631-bacherikov-n.-e.-mikhajjlova-k.-v.-gavenko-v.-l..html |language=Russian |publisher=[[:uk:\u0417\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432'\u044f (\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0435 \u0432\u0438\u0434\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0442\u0432\u043e)|Zdorovja]] |pages=245 |isbn=978-5-311-00334-6 |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDHQPV4D?url=https://www.psyoffice.ru/page,8,3631-bacherikov-n.-e.-mikhajjlova-k.-v.-gavenko-v.-l..html |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Mendelevich |first1=V. D. |last2=Solovieva |first2=S. I. |title=\u041d\u0435\u0432\u0440\u043e\u0437\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u044f \u0438 \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0441\u043e\u043c\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0430 |trans-title=Neurotic disorder in psychosomatic medicine |year=2002 |location=[[Moscow]] |publisher=psytopos.lviv.ua |url=http://psytopos.lviv.ua/downloads/biblioteka/studentam/klinichna/mendelevich_v_d_soloveva_s_l_nevrozologiya_i_psihosomatiches.pdf |pages=505\u20136 |isbn=978-5-901712-27-6 |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDHf73xT?url=http://psytopos.lviv.ua/downloads/biblioteka/studentam/klinichna/mendelevich_v_d_soloveva_s_l_nevrozologiya_i_psihosomatiches.pdf |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=\u0160abrov |first1=A. V. |last2=Solovieva |first2=S. I. |script-title=ru:\u0410\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0439\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u0432 \u0442\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0435\u0432\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0435. \u0420\u0443\u043a\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u043f\u043e \u0434\u0438\u0430\u0433\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0435 \u0438 \u043b\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044e |trans-title=Asthenic disorder in therapeutic practice: A manual to diagnosis and treatment |year=2010 |location=[[Saint Petersburg]] |publisher=libed.ru/knigi-nauka |url=http://libed.ru/knigi-nauka/1078765-1-astenicheskie-rasstroystva-terapevticheskoy-praktike-rukovodstvo-diagnostike-lecheniyu-pod-redakciey-shabrova-solov.php |language=Russian |isbn=978-5-904192-30-3 |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDIbuhnz?url=http://libed.ru/knigi-nauka/1078765-1-astenicheskie-rasstroystva-terapevticheskoy-praktike-rukovodstvo-diagnostike-lecheniyu-pod-redakciey-shabrova-solov.php |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The [[Higher Attestation Commission#Russia and the former Soviet Union|Higher Attestation Commission under the USSR Council of Ministers]] awarded him for this research study the degree of [[Candidate of Sciences]] (1980).<ref>{{cite book |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |year=1980 |script-title=ru: \u041f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0438\u044f \u0438 \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0432 \u0441\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043c\u0435 \u0440\u0435\u0430\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0441 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0437\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u043a\u043b\u0430\u043f\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0430: \u0410\u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0435\u0444\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442 \u0434\u0438\u0441\u0441\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0443\u0447\u0451\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043a\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0438\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u043d\u0430\u0443\u043a |trans-title=Psychotherapy and psychoprophylaxis in the rehabilitation of the patients with prosthetic heart valves: The dissertation on competition of a scientific degree of the candidate of medical sciences |pages=17 |location=[[Kharkov]] |publisher=[[Ministry of Health (Soviet Union)|Ministry of Health of the USSR]] |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m17.html |language=Russian |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDIthUgZ?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m17.html |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> It is a first post-graduate [[academic degree|scientific degree]] in some former [[Eastern Bloc]] countries.\n\n=== Gastroenterology ===\nFrom 1980 to 1990, he worked as professor of [[psychotherapy]] at the [[Kharkiv Medical Academy of Post-graduate Education]]. During this period Skumin investigated [[mental health disorder]] in chronic diseases of the [[Human digestive system|digestive system]] in children and adolescents.<ref name=\"VS91\">{{cite journal |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |year=1991 |title=Borderline mental disorders in chronic diseases of the digestive system in children and adolescents |script-title=ru: Pogranichnye psikhicheskie rasstro\u012dstva pri khronicheskikh bolezniakh pishchevaritel'no\u012d sistemy u dete\u012d i podrostkov |url=https://usyd.summon.serialssolutions.com/search?q=Skumin#!/search/document?ho=t&l=en-AU&q=AuthorCombined:%22Skumin,%20V%20A%22&id=FETCHMERGED-pubmed_primary_16615262 |journal=Zhurnal Nevropatologii I Psikhiatrii Imeni S.S. Korsakova (Moscow, Russia : 1952) |volume=91 |issue=8 |pages=81\u20134 |oclc=117464823 |pmid=1661526 |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDW85N5k?url=https://summon.altmetric.com/details/4994563#!/search/document?ho=t&l=en-AU&q=AuthorCombined:%22Skumin,%20V%20A%22&id=FETCHMERGED-pubmed_primary_16615262 |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nA most significant life event in the first years of life is a disease, especially if it is of early onset, severe, life-threatening, with an uncertain prognosis, and with the necessity of frequent diagnostic and therapeutic interventions. Psychological implications are a significant part of the illness, not a marginal component; they can affect prognosis and outcome. Various laboratory tests, [[physical examination]]s, and surgeries on these individuals show no evidence supporting the idea that these exaggerating [[symptom]]s are present.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/ms84.html |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |year=1984 |script-title=ru: Deontologiia v rabote meditsinsko\u012d sestry detsko\u012d bol'nitsy |trans-title=Deontology in the work of a pediatric hospital nurse |journal=Med Sestra |volume=43 |issue=2 |pages=59\u201361 |oclc=113171929 |pmid=6561382 |title=Deontology in the work of a pediatric hospital nurse |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDfAfktc?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/ms84.html |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last2=Skumin |first2=V. A. |last1=Belousov |first1=Iu. V. |title=Psychotherapeutic aspects of the rehabilitation of children with chronic diseases of the digestive system |year=1986 |script-title=ru: Psikhoterapevticheskie aspekty reabilitatsii dete\u012d s khronicheskimi zabolevaniiami pishchevaritel'no\u012d sistemy |trans-title=Psychotherapeutic aspects of the rehabilitation of children with chronic diseases of the digestive system |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/articles/pediatriia.html |journal=Pediatriia |volume=8 |issue=8 |pages=46\u201350 |oclc=116853253 |pmid=3763350 |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDfi3bb3?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/articles/pediatriia.html |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn particular, Skumin studied the patients, aged from 6 to 17, suffering from diseases of the gastrointestinal tract. Most of them have revealed a negative psychological attitude to the dietotherapy they received. A system of special measures has been developed including three main elements: (1) psychotherapeutic mediation of dietotherapy before its administration and in the process of the therapy; (2) creation of the psychologic attitude to the diet adherence; (3) alteration of the patient's taste stereotype. Realization of such measures has been conducive to higher effectiveness of the dietotherapy.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Skumin |first=VA |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/voprpitan.html |script-title=ru: Psikhologicheskie aspekty lechebnogo pitaniia dete\u012d i podrostkov, stradaiushchikh bolezniami pishchevaritel'no\u012d sistemy |trans-title=Psychological aspects of diet therapy of children and adolescents suffering from digestive system diseases |year=1987 |language=Russian |oclc=116648174 |pmid=3439083 |journal=Voprosy Pitaniya |issue=6 |pages=26\u20139 |title=Psychological aspects of diet therapy of children and adolescents suffering from digestive system diseases |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDg5nL7Y?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/voprpitan.html |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nBased on studies into the mental sphere of gastroenterological [[patient]]s, he systematized borderline [[Neurosis|neurotic]] and [[personality disorders]] on the clinical and etiopathogenetic basis. He studied the psychosocial problems that may affect children or teenagers who have the chronic gastrointestinal disease. A system of measures aimed at early [[diagnosis]], correction, [[therapy]] and [[prophylaxis]] of borderline conditions and psychosocial readaptation of patients is scientifically based. The main result of his scientific activity was the discovery of the \"[[syndrome]] of the neurotic phantom of somatic disease\"<ref name=\"VS91\"/> (a specific psychopathological complex of [[symptom]]s) and a \"concept of the mental constituent of a chronic somatic disease\".<ref>{{cite book |last4=Skumin |first4=V. A. |last3=Filatov |first3=A. T. |last2=Belousov |first2=Yu. V. |last1=Lukyanova |first1=E. M. |year=1986 |script-title=ru: \u0418\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0438\u0438 \u0432 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u043d\u043e\u043c \u043b\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u0445\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0438\u0449\u0435\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043c\u044b \u0443 \u0434\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0439: M\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 |trans-title=The use of psychotherapy in the treatment of chronic diseases of the digestive system in children: Methodical recommendations |location=[[Kiev]] |publisher=[[Ministry of Healthcare (Ukraine)|Ministry of Healthcare of Ukrainian SSR]] |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m14.html |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDhOVl3t?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m14.html |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all |author1-link=:ru:\u041b\u0443\u043a\u044c\u044f\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430, \u0415\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0439\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0430 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last2=Skumin |first2=V. A. |last1=Belousov |first1=Yu. V. |year=1987 |script-title=ru: \u041f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0438\u044f \u0432 \u0434\u0435\u0442\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u044d\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0438: \u0423\u0447\u0435\u0431\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043e\u0431\u0438\u0435 |trans-title=Psychotherapy in Pediatric Gastroenterology: Tutorial |location=[[Moscow]] |publisher=[[Ministry of Health (Soviet Union)|Ministry of Health of the USSR]] |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m1.html |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDhs3NZ7?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m1.html |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://ru.science.wikia.com/wiki/\u041f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f_\u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043b\u044f\u044e\u0449\u0430\u044f_\u0441\u043e\u043c\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439_\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0437\u043d\u0438 |title=\u041f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043b\u044f\u044e\u0449\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043e\u043c\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0437\u043d\u0438 |trans-title=The mental constituent of a chronic somatic disease |publisher=science.wikia.com |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDiDouvg?url=http://ru.science.wikia.com/wiki/%D0%9F%D1%81%D0%B8%D1%85%D0%B8%D1%87%D0%B5%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B0%D1%8F_%D1%81%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B0%D0%B2%D0%BB%D1%8F%D1%8E%D1%89%D0%B0%D1%8F_%D1%81%D0%BE%D0%BC%D0%B0%D1%82%D0%B8%D1%87%D0%B5%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%B9_%D0%B1%D0 |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nSkumin defended his doctoral thesis in Moscow at [[Serbsky Center|the Serbsky State Scientific Center for Social and Forensic Psychiatry]] (1988). The [[Higher Attestation Commission]] awarded him for this research study the degree of [[Doktor Nauk]] in Medicine ([[Doctor of Science|Doctor of Medical Sciences \u2013 Dr.scient.med.]]).<ref>{{cite book |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |script-title=ru: \u041f\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0439\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u0443 \u0434\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0439 \u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u0441 \u0445\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u043c\u0438 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0437\u043d\u044f\u043c\u0438 \u043f\u0438\u0449\u0435\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043c\u044b (\u043a\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430, \u0441\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043c\u0430\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430, \u043b\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435, \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430). \u0410\u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0435\u0444\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442 \u0434\u0438\u0441\u0441\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0443\u0447\u0451\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0434\u043e\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0430 \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u043d\u0430\u0443\u043a |trans-title=Border mental disorders in children and adolescents with chronic diseases of the digestive system (clinic, systematics, treatment, psychoprophylaxis). The dissertation on competition of a scientific degree of the doctor of medical sciences |year=1988 |location=[[Moscow]] |publisher=[[Ministry of Health (Soviet Union)|Ministry of Health of the USSR]] |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m16.html |language=Russian |accessdate=4 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wDiqSvhK?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m16.html |archivedate=4 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> It is a higher [[doctoral degree]] which may be earned after the [[Candidate of Sciences]] (which is informally regarded in [[Russia]] and many other [[post-Soviet states]] as equivalent to [[PhD]] obtained in countries in which PhD is not the highest [[academic degree]]).\n\n==Culture of Health and other contributions==\n{{Quote box\n|width     = 22em\n|border    = 4px\n|align     = left\n|bgcolor   =#D0F0C0\n|fontsize  = 105%\n|quote     = The Culture of Health is the basic science about ''Spiritual Humanity''. It studies the perspectives of  harmonious development of ''Spiritual man'' and ''Spiritual ethnos'' as a conscious creator of the ''State of Light'' into the territory of the [[Solar System]].\n|salign    = right\n|source    =&nbsp;\u2014Victor Skumin<ref>{{cite book |year=2013 |url=http://sovieteramuseum.com/?product=art-works-by-russian-cosmism-painter-xx-xxi-ct-catalogue-of-exhibition-2013 |title=Art works by Russian cosmism painter XX \u2013 XXI ct. Catalogue of exhibition 2013 |publisher=Roerich museum |accessdate=28 October 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6qGPQz1bk? |archivedate=6 May 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://900igr.net/prezentatsii/fizkultura/Kultura-zdorovja/007-Kultura-zdorovja-fundamentalnaja-nauka-o-Dukhovnom-CHelovechestve.html |year=2009 |author=Kovaleva E. A. |title=\u041f\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0441\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442. \u041a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430 \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u044f \u0443\u0447\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0445\u0441\u044f \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0444\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u0435\u0441\u0431\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0433\u0430\u044e\u0449\u0435\u0439 \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0434\u044b \u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044b. \u0421\u043b\u0430\u0439\u0434 7 |trans-title=Pedagogical Council. Slide 7 of the presentation \"culture of health\" to the lessons of physical education on the theme the \"Health\" |publisher=900igr.net |accessdate=28 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wH2YJ5wh? |archivedate=6 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n}}\n\nFrom 1990 to 1994, Skumin held positions as Professor by the Chair of [[Psychology]] and [[Pedagogy]], and Professor by the Chair of [[Physical Education]] and Health life at the [[Kharkiv State Academy of Culture#Notable people|Kharkiv State Academy of Culture]]. Skumin completed research of theoretical and practical issues of culture of health, which he developed throughout his scientific and pedagogical activity. These methods, he has introduced in the training course for the students of the Academy: ''The Foundations of a Culture of Health''.<ref>{{cite newspaper |date=1992 |volume=8 |journal=[[:lt:Gydytoj\u0173 \u017einios|Gydytoj\u0173 \u017einios]] |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/articles/g892.html |last=Skumin |first=V.A. |title=Yoga, society and culture |trans-title=Yoga, visuomen\u0117 ir kult\u016bra |accessdate=8 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wJTTCVuz?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/articles/g892.html |archivedate=8 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\nHis scientific and pedagogical work Skumin combine with a social activity. In 1994, he was elected to the post of the President-founder of the [[Roerichism#The World Organisation of Culture of Health (WOCH)|World Organisation of Culture of Health (WOCH)]] \u2014 International social movement \"To Health via Culture\" ({{lang-ru|\u041c\u0435\u0436\u0434\u0443\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0301\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0301\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u0414\u0432\u0438\u0436\u0435\u0301\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u00ab\u041a \u0417\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0301\u0432\u044c\u044e \u0447\u0435\u0301\u0440\u0435\u0437 \u041a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0301\u0440\u0443}}). Coat of arms of the WOCH contain a symbol of [[Roerichism]].\n\nThe organization operates in accordance with the registered in [[Ministry of Justice (Russia)|Ministry of Justice of the Russian Federation]] Charter. Key element of a Culture of Health is implement innovative health programs that support a holistic approach to physical, mental and spiritual well-being both inside and outside the workplace.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kult-zdor.ru/?page_id=824 |title=Charter of the World Organisation of Culture of Health (Russian: \u0423\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432) |publisher=Kult-zdor.ru |accessdate=18 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6poMifaLN?url=http://kult-zdor.ru/?page_id=824 |archivedate=18 April 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://kult-zdor.ru/?page_id=5 |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |title=Culture of health is a science of future |publisher=Kult-zdor.ru |accessdate=10 November 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wFXbtCDp?url=http://kult-zdor.ru/?page_id=5 |archivedate=5 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Theosophie.jpg |thumb |185px |left |<center>Symbol of [[Theosophical Society]] incorporated the [[Swastika]], [[Star of David]], [[Ankh]], [[Om|Aum]] and [[Ouroboros]] symbols</center>]]\n{{multiple image\n| align = left\n| image1 = Helena Petrovna Blavatsky.jpg \n| width1 = 150 \n| alt1 = \n| caption1 = \n| image2 = Helena Roerich 1.jpg \n| width2 = 160 \n| alt2 = \n| caption2 = \n| footer = <center>Two philosophers greatly influenced the New Age movement: [[Helena Blavatsky]] (left) and [[Helena Roerich]]</center>\n}}\n\nIn the [[Russian Orthodox Church]] the social activities of this international organization qualifies as an ideology of the [[Living Ethics]] and [[New Age]] (NA),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orthodox-institute.ru/biblioteka/materialyi-po-sektovedeniyu/okkultizm/grantsev-v.i.-kriticheskiy-analiz-ideologii-nyu-eydzh-i-otsenka-ee-obschestvennoy-opasnosti/ |last=Grantzev |first=V. I. |title=\u041a\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0437 \u0438\u0434\u0435\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0438 \"\u041d\u044c\u044e \u042d\u0439\u0434\u0436\" \u0438 \u043e\u0446\u0435\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u0435\u0451 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u043f\u0430\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 |trans-title=A critical analysis of the ideology of the \"New Age\" and an assessment of its threat to society |publisher=Orthodox-institute.ru |accessdate=18 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6ppo9bwbU?url=http://www.orthodox-institute.ru/biblioteka/materialyi-po-sektovedeniyu/okkultizm/grantsev-v.i.-kriticheskiy-analiz-ideologii-nyu-eydzh-i-otsenka-ee-obschestvennoy-opasnosti/ |archivedate=19 April 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scienceandapologetics.org/text/85.htm |last=Grantzev |first=V. I. |title=\u041a\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0437 \u0438\u0434\u0435\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0438 \"\u041d\u044c\u044e \u042d\u0439\u0434\u0436\" \u0438 \u043e\u0446\u0435\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u0435\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u043f\u0430\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438. \u0422\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0442 |trans-title=A critical analysis of the ideology of the \"New Age\" and an assessment of its threat to society. Text |publisher=www.scienceandapologetics.org |accessdate=18 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wFYIWHqW?url=http://www.scienceandapologetics.org/text/85.htm |archivedate=5 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n{{quote|The ideology of the NA serves outstanding contemporary philosophers: [[Gregory Bateson]], [[Ken Wilber]], [[Paul Feyerabend]]. On a grand scale is the creation and support of international organizations, contained in the ideology of the NA. In [[Russia]] and in [[Ukraine]], International movement \"To Health via Culture\", based on the teachings of Agni Yoga, operates and has a great publishing activity.}}\n\nThe relationship between the Skumin's doctrine and [[Roerichism]] is also confirmed by some scientists, such as Goraschuk V. P., Professor of [[H.S. Skovoroda Kharkiv National Pedagogical University]]. In 2004, he wrote in his thesis for a Doctor\u2019s degree on speciality \"general pedagogics and history of pedagogics\",<ref>{{cite book |last=Goraschuk |first=V. P. |script-title=uk: \u0422\u0435\u043e\u0440\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0447\u043d\u0456 \u0456 \u043c\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0434\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0456\u0447\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0443\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u043a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0438 \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u2019\u044f \u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044f\u0440\u0456\u0432. \u0414\u0438\u0441\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0456\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0431\u0443\u0442\u0442\u044f \u043d\u0430\u0443\u043a\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u0435\u043d\u044f \u0434\u043e\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0430 \u043f\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0433\u0456\u0447\u043d\u0438\u0445 \u043d\u0430\u0443\u043a \u0456\u0437 \u0441\u043f\u0435\u0446\u0456\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0456 13.00.01 \u2013 \u0437\u0430\u0433\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0433\u0456\u043a\u0430 \u0442\u0430 \u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0456\u044f \u043f\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0433\u0456\u043a\u0438 |trans-title=Theoretical and methodological principles of pupils\u2019 health culture forming. Thesis for a Doctor\u2019s degree on speciality 13.00.01 \u2013 general pedagogics and history of pedagogics |year=2004 |location=[[Kharkov]] |publisher=avtoreferat.net |url=http://avtoreferat.net/content/view/9282/52/ |language=Ukrainian |accessdate=5 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wFYd8uBZ?url=http://avtoreferat.net/content/view/9282/52/ |archivedate=5 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|V. Skum\u00ecn developed the problems associated with a culture of health in the context of [[Roerichism|philosophy of Roerich]].}}\n\n[[Agni Yoga]] is a philosophical teaching which embraces all sides of being\u2014from cosmological problems, down to daily human life. This teaching is based on the books written by [[Helena Roerich|Helena]] and [[Nicholas Roerich]] in the first half of the 20th century.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.agniyoga.org/ |title=Agni Yoga Society |accessdate=6 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6p2NfrZqP?url=http://www.agniyoga.org/index.php |archivedate=17 March 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The New Age movement is a [[spirituality|spiritual]] movement that developed in [[Western culture|Western nations]] during the 1970s. The movement is characterised by a [[holism|holistic]] view of the cosmos, a belief in an emergent [[Age of Aquarius]] an emphasis on self-spirituality and the authority of the self, a focus on healing (particularly with [[Alternative medicine|alternative therapies]]).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://wrldrels.org/ARTICLES/NEW%20AGE/New%20Age%20Transformed.pdf |author=J. Gordon Melton |title=New Age Transformed |publisher=wrldrels.org |accessdate=5 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wFZAJwr0?url=http://wrldrels.org/ARTICLES/NEW%20AGE/New%20Age%20Transformed.pdf |archivedate=5 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all|author-link=J. Gordon Melton}}</ref>\n\nProfessor Verhorubova and professor Lobanova from [[Tomsk State Pedagogical University]] argued (2012) that in accordance with the concept of a culture of health, proposed by Skumin, the culture  \u2013 spiritual, mental, and physical \u2013  determines the status of human health. And health \u2013 spiritual, mental, physical \u2013 is a prerequisite for achieving a higher level of culture.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cyberleninka.ru/article/n/mnogoobrazie-opredeleniy-fenomena-kultura-zdorovya-kak-pokazatel-ego-mnogogrannosti-v-pedagogicheskom-obrazovanii |last2=Lobanova |first2=N. A. |last1=Verhorubova |first=O. V. |title=\u041c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0438\u0435 \u043e\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0444\u0435\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0430 \"\u043a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430 \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u044f\" \u043a\u0430\u043a \u043f\u043e\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c \u0435\u0433\u043e \u043c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0432 \u043f\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u043c \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0438 |trans-title=The diversity of definitions the phenomenon of \"culture of health\" as an indicator of its versatility in education |publisher=\u0412\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043d\u0438\u043a \u0422\u043e\u043c\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043f\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0433\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0443\u043d\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442\u0430 |year=2012 |volume=5 |pages=161\u20135 |accessdate=10 November 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6cKKxNxWb?url=http://cyberleninka.ru/article/n/mnogoobrazie-opredeleniy-fenomena-kultura-zdorovya-kak-pokazatel-ego-mnogogrannosti-v-pedagogicheskom-obrazovanii |archivedate=16 October 2015 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe essence of the teachings of the culture of health, reveals professor of [[University of Luhansk]] N. Gribok. He wrote at 2009,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cyberleninka.ru/article/n/suschestvennaya-harakteristika-kultury-zdorovya-studentov-spetsialnoy-meditsinskoy-gruppy |last=Gribok |first=N. N. |title=\u0421\u0423\u0422\u041d\u0406\u0421\u041d\u0410 \u0425\u0410\u0420\u0410\u041a\u0422\u0415\u0420\u0418\u0421\u0422\u0418\u041a\u0410 \u041a\u0423\u041b\u042c\u0422\u0423\u0420\u0418 \u0417\u0414\u041e\u0420\u041e\u0412'\u042f \u0421\u0422\u0423\u0414\u0415\u041d\u0422\u0406\u0412 \u0421\u041f\u0415\u0426\u0406\u0410\u041b\u042c\u041d\u041e\u0407 \u041c\u0415\u0414\u0418\u0427\u041d\u041e\u0407 \u0413\u0420\u0423\u041f\u0418 |trans-title=The essential characteristic of the culture of health students special medical groups |publisher=cyberleninka.ru |date=2009 |accessdate=6 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6cKLOpOiw?url=http://cyberleninka.ru/article/n/suschestvennaya-harakteristika-kultury-zdorovya-studentov-spetsialnoy-meditsinskoy-gruppy |archivedate=16 October 2015 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|Russian Professor Skumin insists on the fact that the culture of health should be considered as an integral part of the spiritual culture and the moral culture, culture of labour and culture of recreation, culture of personality and culture of relationships. According to the scientist, the culture of health is not only the mechanical connection of the two concepts\u2014the concept of \u2033culture\u2033 and the concept of \u2033health\u2033. This is their synthesis, which forms a new quality, a new content. Skumin examines the culture of health as the specific science, that develops the theoretical and practical tasks of harmonious development of the spiritual, mental, and physical human force, forming of optimum  environment, which provides a higher level of creativity of life. Thus, Skumin argues that the culture of health is a separate science, that creates new content. The main challenge of culture of health is the development of spiritual, mental and physical capabilities of man.}}\n\nThe Culture of Health means recognizing health\u2019s central importance in the lives. Expounding the philosophical aspects of his Doctrine of Culture of Health, Skumin referred to the works of [[Helena Blavatsky]], Helena and Nicholas Roerich, [[Konstantin Tsiolkovsky]], and [[Alexander Chizhevsky]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed?term=Skumin%20V |title=PubMed : Skumin VA |publisher=Ncbi.nlm.nih.gov |accessdate=6 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wG8vnfMJ?url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed?term=Skumin%20V |archivedate=6 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://biblus.ru/Default.aspx?auth=1b0696g4 |title=BIBLUS : Victor Skumin |publisher=Biblus.ru |accessdate=6 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wG97njUk?url=http://biblus.ru/Default.aspx?auth=1b0696g4 |archivedate=6 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref> In some of his publications, he argues that the Culture of Health will play an important role in the creation of a human spiritual society into the [[Solar System]].\n\nHe elaborated on the [[Spiritual evolution#Theosophical conceptions|theosophical conceptions]] of [[spiritual evolution]] and proposed (1990) a classification of '''''Homo spiritalis''''' ([[Latin]]: ''spiritual man''), [[Root race#the sixth root race|the sixth root race]], consisting of eight sub-races (subspecies) \u2013 HS0 Anabiosis spiritalis, HS1 Scientella spiritalis, HS2 Aurora spiritalis, HS3 Ascensus spiritalis, HS4 Vocatus spiritalis, HS5 Illuminatio spiritalis, \u041dS6 Creatio spiritalis, and HS7 Servitus spiritalis.<ref>{{cite book |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |script-title=ru:\u0427\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a \u0434\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0432\u043d\u044b\u0439: \u0440\u043e\u043b\u044c \u043a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u044b \u0434\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u044f \u0432 \u0443\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0440\u0430\u0441\u044b \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0442\u0435 |trans-title=Spiritual man: The role of the Culture of spiritual health for approval of the new human race on the planet |year=1996 |publisher=theeuropeanlibrary.org |url=http://www.theeuropeanlibrary.org/tel4/record/3000010564370?query=%D0%B2%D0%B8%D0%BA%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80+%D1%81%D0%BA%D1%83%D0%BC%D0%B8%D0%BD+ |language=Russian |isbn=978-5-88167-012-2 |accessdate=29 May 2019 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/78jMM5dws?url=http://www.theeuropeanlibrary.org/tel4/record/3000010564370?query=%D0%B2%D0%B8%D0%BA%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80+%D1%81%D0%BA%D1%83%D0%BC%D0%B8%D0%BD+ |archivedate=29 May 2019 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Literary and publishing activities==\nSkumin wrote several books of fiction, and also essays.<ref>{{cite book |last2=Aunovsky |first2=O. K. |last1=Skumin |first1=V. A. |year=1995 |script-title=ru: \u0421\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0446\u044b (\u043e \u0441\u0435\u043c\u044c\u0435 \u0420\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0432) |trans-title=The Bringers of the Light (The story of the Roerich family) |location=[[Novocheboksarsk]] |publisher=TEROS |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/svet.html |isbn=978-5-88167-004-7 |language=Russian |accessdate=10 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6t3vBmhIG?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/svet.html |archivedate=28 August 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |script-title=ru: \u041e \u0431\u044b\u043b\u043e\u043c \u0438 \u0433\u0440\u044f\u0434\u0443\u0449\u0435\u043c: \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0447\u0438 |trans-title=About the past and the future: Parables for meditation. |year=1997 |location=Novocheboksarsk |publisher=TEROS |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/mp.html |isbn=978-5-88167-016-0 |language=Russian |accessdate=7 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wIU11ZrJ?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/mp.html |archivedate=7 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |script-title=ru: \u0410\u0444\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0437\u043c\u044b \u0410\u0433\u043d\u0438 \u0419\u043e\u0433\u0438 |trans-title=Sutras of Agni Yoga. |year=1995 |location=Novocheboksarsk |publisher=TEROS |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/af.html |language=Russian |isbn=978-5-88167-007-8 |accessdate=12 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wIUCotb1?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/af.html |archivedate=7 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |script-title=ru: \u041b\u0435\u0433\u0435\u043d\u0434\u044b, \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0447\u0438, \u0441\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0410\u0433\u043d\u0438 \u0419\u043e\u0433\u0438 |trans-title=Legends, parables, and stories of Agni Yoga |year=1995 |location=Novocheboksarsk |publisher=TEROS |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/legenda.html |language=Russian |isbn=978-5-88167-008-5 |accessdate=24 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wIUZcNij?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/legenda.html |archivedate=7 January 2018 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/j9.html |title=\u0423\u0434\u0440\u0430\u044f \u2014 \u043d\u0430\u0448 \u0414\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0432\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u041d\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043a |trans-title=Udraia (George Roerich's spiritual name) is our Guru |author=Skumin VA |year=2003 |journal=To Health Via Culture |volume=9 |pages=3\u201312 |issn=0204-3440 |accessdate=14 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6vmc0Rh13?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/j9.html |archivedate=17 December 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/j10_1.html |title=\u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f |trans-title=Russia |author=Skumin VA |year=2004 |journal=To Health Via Culture |volume=10 |pages=3\u20136 |issn=0204-3440 |accessdate=7 January 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6swKPbp4I?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/j10_1.html |archivedate=23 August 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/j10_2.html |title=\u0424\u0443\u044f\u043c\u0430 \u2014 \u043e\u0433\u043d\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0413\u0443\u0440\u0443-\u041f\u043e\u043a\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c \u0434\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 |trans-title=Fuyama (N. Roerich's spiritual name) is a Fiery Guru-patron of spiritual humanity |author=Skumin VA |year=2004 |journal=To Health Via Culture |volume=10 |pages=31\u201334 |issn=0204-3440 |accessdate=21 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6vmbpbde2?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/j10_2.html |archivedate=17 December 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref> He is the author of music and lyrics of several songs.<ref>{{cite book |last=Skumin |first=Victor |script-title=ru: \u041c\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0432\u044b, \u0433\u0438\u043c\u043d\u044b, \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0447\u0438 \u041a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u044b \u0417\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u044f |trans-title=Culture of Health: prayers, hymns, parables. |year=2002 |location=[[Cheboksary]] |publisher=To Health via Culture |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m.html |language=Russian |isbn=978-5-88167-018-4 |accessdate=18 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6vmcES03C?url=http://biblmdkz.ru/m.html |archivedate=17 December 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Among them anthem [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kyknqmZhyIk \"To Health via Culture\"]. This anthem consists of four stanzas. The capital letters each of the four stanzas form the word [[Agni]].<ref name=\"Gimns of Culture of Health\">{{cite book |last=Skumin |first=Victor |script-title=ru: \u0413\u0438\u043c\u043d\u044b \u041a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u044b \u0417\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u044c\u044f |trans-title=Gimns of Culture of Health |year=2007 |location=[[Cheboksary]] |publisher=To Health via Culture |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/gimn.html |language=Russian |isbn=978-5-88167-030-6 |accessdate=6 February 2020 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6vmcoqT4R?url=https://biblmdkz.ru/gimn.html |archivedate=17 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 1995, Skumin became the first [[editor-in-chief]] (EIC) of the journal ''To Health via Culture''. This journal of the World Organisation of Culture of Health (\u2033World Health Culture Organization\u2033) received an [[International Standard Serial Number]] (ISSN) 0204-3440. The main topics of the magazine are the dissemination of ideas of [[Self care#Culture of Health|Culture of Health]], [[holistic medicine]], and [[Roerichism]].<ref>{{cite book |url=https://catalog.loc.gov/vwebv/search?searchCode=STNO&searchType=1&recCount=25&searchArg=0204-3440 |title=K zdorov\u02b9i\ufe20u\ufe21 cherez kul\u02b9turu: zhurnal Mezhdunarodnogo obshchestvennogo dvizhenii\ufe20a\ufe21 \"K zdorov\u02b9i\ufe20u\ufe21 cherez kul\u02b9turu\" |trans-title=To health via culture: journal of the World Health Culture Organization |publisher=catalog.loc.gov |oclc=70966742 |accessdate=18 November 2018 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6pppaZG8a?url=https://catalog.loc.gov/vwebv/search?searchCode=STNO&searchType=1&recCount=25&searchArg=0204-3440 |archivedate=19 April 2017 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Organization also has its own publishing house (\"To Health via Culture\").<ref>{{cite web |url=http://biblmdkz.ru/knigi.html |title=The Library of Culture of Health |publisher=biblmdkz.ru |accessdate=16 June 2019}}</ref>\n\nSkumin wrote many books and articles on a variety medical and spiritual topics advocating a holistic approach to health. He is the author or co-author of a series illustrated books on the culture of health, yoga, and Roerichism.<ref>{{YouTube|JA8D5_tBeNQ |Olga Aunovsky, Winner of the Nicholas Roerich International Prize: Skumin's doctrine of the culture of health. Part 1}} {{in lang|ru}}\n* {{YouTube |AGHoqMoLCeI | \u2014 Part 2}} \n* {{YouTube |qeOG8RrJGG8 | \u2014 Part 3}} \n* {{YouTube |gUBu50_GKv8 | \u2014 Part 4}}</ref>\n\n{{Collapse top|Selected bibliography}}\n* {{cite book |last=Skumin |first=V. A. |script-title=ru: \u041f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043f\u0438\u044f \u0438 \u043f\u0441\u0438\u0445\u043e\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0432 \u0441\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043c\u0435 \u0440\u0435\u0430\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0441 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0435\u0437\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u043a\u043b\u0430\u043f\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0430: \u0410\u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0435\u0444\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442 \u0434\u0438\u0441\u0441\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u043e\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0443\u0447\u0451\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043a\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0438\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u043d\u0430\u0443\u043a |trans-title=Psychotherapy and psychoprophylaxis in the rehabilitation of the patients with prosthetic heart valves: The dissertation on competition of a scientific degree of the candidate of medical sciences |yea