ast radio stations in the Memphis area include, but are not limited to:\n\n===FM stations===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Call sign !! Frequency !! City of License <ref>[http://www.fcc.gov/mb/audio/fmq.html FM Query - FM Radio Technical Information - Audio Division (FCC) USA<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090825071957/http://www.fcc.gov/mb/audio/fmq.html |date=August 25, 2009 }}</ref> !! Owner!! Slogan !! Format <ref>[http://www.arbitron.com/radio_stations/station_information.htm Station Information Profile<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n|-\n|[[WQOX]] || <span style=\"display:none\">0</span>88.5 FM || Memphis|| Shelby County Schools (Grades K-12)||88.5 the Voice of SCS  || Urban Adult Contemporary\n|-\n|[[WYPL]] || <span style=\"display:none\">0</span>89.3 FM || Memphis|| Memphis Public Library & Information Center||Memphis Public Library Reading Radio || Radio Reading Service\n|-\n|[[WEVL]] || <span style=\"display:none\">0</span>89.9 FM || Memphis|| Southern Communication Volunteers, Inc.||Volunteer, Member Supported Radio ||Variety\n|-\n|[[WKNO-FM|WKNO]] || <span style=\"display:none\">0</span>91.1 FM || Memphis|| Mid-South Public Communications Foundation|| WKNO NPR For the Mid South ||Public Radio\n|-\n|[[WUMR]] || <span style=\"display:none\">0</span>91.7 FM||Memphis || University of Memphis||U92 Jazz || Jazz\n|-\n|[[WMFS-FM|WMFS]] || <span style=\"display:none\">0</span>92.9 FM|| Bartlett||[[Entercom]] ||ESPN Radio ||Sports\n|-\n|[[WLFP]] || <span style=\"display:none\">0</span>94.1 FM||Germantown||[[Entercom]] ||The Wolf||Country\n|-\n|[[WHAL-FM|WHAL]] || <span style=\"display:none\">0</span>95.7 FM||Hornlake, MS||[[iHeartMedia, Inc.]] ||Hallelujah|| Urban Gospel\n|-\n|[[WHRK]] || <span style=\"display:none\">0</span>97.1 FM||Memphis ||[[iHeartMedia, Inc.]] ||K97.1 || Hip Hop\n|-\n|[[WXMX]] || <span style=\"display:none\">0</span>98.1 FM||Millington||[[Cumulus Media]] ||The Max ||Rock\n|-\n|[[WKIM]]